DUBAI: The UAE health ministry announced 2,084 new coronavirus cases and five virus-related deaths over the past 24 hours. The ministry's daily briefing said the newly identified coronavirus cases bring the total number of recorded cases in the UAE to 847,142. It also said the infected individuals are from various nationalities, are in a stable condition, and receiving the necessary care. The five death cases  reported were due to COVID-19 complications, bringing the total number of deaths in the country to 2,248. It  also noted that an additional 1,067 individuals had fully recovered from COVID-19, bringing the total number of recoveries to 778,163.